1. The sudo class focus is meant to be used for when an individual places their cursor within an input field so they can begin typing.
Once the input field is selected typically a blue outline appears, we can customize this using the focus sudo class.

2. HTML
  <div class="form__group">
           <input type="text" class="form__input" placeholder="Full Name" id="name" required>
           <label for="name" class="form__label">Full Name</label>
  </div>

3.CSS

.form__input {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  font-family: inherit;
  color: inherit;
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
  border-radius: .2rem;
  background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  border: none;
  border-bottom: .3rem solid transparent;
  width: 90%;
  display: block; 
  }
  .form__input:focus {
    outline: none;
    box-shadow: o 1rem 2rem rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border-bottom: 0.3rem solid #55c57a; 
    }

